# L2-SYN-018 fixture: 1 KB of 0x20-fill. `0x20 0x20` parses as a
# valid SPURIOUS_DATA Type Word (msg_type=0x20, wc=32) and the
# two-record look-ahead admits it; without the homogeneous-payload
# defense the reader would emit a torrent of synthetic 64-byte
# SPURIOUS_DATA frames. Both modes SHALL reject the input with
# MieError::HomogeneousPayload / MieHomogeneousPayloadError and exit 2
# (same exit-code class as MieNoValidRecordsError — a "wrong file
# type" rejection rather than a per-record failure).

